{"id": "bcrjp5", "title": "Only 55% of boomers have retirement savings.", "selftext": "Many baby boomers are in serious trouble because they didn\u2019t save enough money. Only 55% of boomers have retirement savings. Those who don\u2019t will need to rely on social security and pensions if they have one. \n\n23% said they never had retirement savings. That means they never made enough money to have extra to save or they splurged their earnings on unnecessary items.You can prudently spend some money today because you never know how long your life will be. Plus, you can enjoy the money better when you are younger. However, you need to save money if you have it. Learn from boomers\u2019 mistakes. 17% said they don\u2019t have retirement savings, but once did. They might have spent their savings or borrowed against their IRA because an unexpected expense came up.\u00a0\n\nOf the boomers with retirement savings, 28% have less than $100,000. That\u2019s not enough to retire on.The average 65-74 year old spends $55,000 per year. Only 58% of the boomers with savings said they have over $100,000 saved. Very few are adequately prepared for retirement.\n\n[A Great GDP Doesn\u2019t Solve Retirement Crisis](https://upfina.com/a-great-gdp-doesnt-solve-retirement-crisis/)\n\n[Percent of boomers with savings ](https://i.imgur.com/pVDliMF.jpg)\n\n[Amount boomers have saved](https://i.imgur.com/R5JBeps.jpg)", "created_utc": 1555168757, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/bcrjp5/only_55_of_boomers_have_retirement_savings/", "is_self": true}